🔍 Use Case #2: Automated Communication Intelligence
Business Problem
The External Communications team faces an overload of:
•	Incoming inquiries from media, public, and stakeholders
•	The need to constantly monitor public sentiment on monetary policy, central bank actions, and macroeconomic conditions
This creates a bottleneck for:
•	Timely responses
•	Consistent messaging
•	Early detection of reputational risk
•	Data-driven communication strategy 
🎯 Hackathon Goal
Build an AI system that becomes a virtual assistant for the Communications team by automating:
1.	Classification of incoming emails/queries
2.	Drafting standard responses for recurring categories
3.	Sentiment analysis on public discourse
4.	Trending-topic detection across media + social
5.	Communication risk alerts
6.	Automated communication insights dashboard/reporting 
🌟 What Product Are We Actually Envisioning?
A single unified interface that ingests an inquiry, performs full NLP analysis (classification, sentiment, topics), generates a safe draft response, and displays an insights dashboard with sentiment trends, topic clouds, and risk alerts — all wrapped in basic RAI controls and explainability.
⭐ MVP Definition 
This must deliver three value pillars:
Pillar 1 — Automated Inquiry Understanding
•	Text classification
•	Sentiment analysis
•	Topic modeling
•	Key phrase extraction
For a Federal Reserve team, classification+sentiment+topic are the minimum needed to determine:
•	Whether a message signals market sensitivity
•	Whether there is coordinated sentiment activity
•	Whether misinformation or policy confusion is trending
Pillar 2 — AI Draft Response Generation
For a Fed communications team, consistency and accuracy are essential.
An MVP must provide:
•	A safe, neutral, professional draft
•	A human-in-the-loop review space
•	A clear explanation of the response basis

Pillar 3 — Insight Layer 
Your file’s architecture and UI include an Insights Aggregator Layer and a Dashboard/UI layer with:
•	Sentiment trend graph
•	Trending topics cloud
•	Risk alerts

Why essential for the Federal Reserve?
•	Sentiment trend shifts may signal the start of misinformation waves
•	Topic spikes may indicate coordinated narratives
•	Risk indicators must be surfaced immediately for leadership
A true MVP for an external comms use case must enable leadership awareness, even in a basic form.


Key Product components
1. Ingestion
•	Manual paste OR simple upload
•	Stored in a minimal storage layer (S3)
2. Automated NLP Analysis
•	Category
•	Sentiment
•	Topic modeling
•	(Optional but recommended: key phrase extraction)
3. LLM Draft Response Panel
•	Editable draft
•	Clear explainability note
•	RAI safeguards (“no policy predictions,” etc.)
4. Insights Dashboard
•	Sentiment trend line (last 7 days or customizable time periods)
•	Trending topics cloud
•	Risk alerts

⭐ What Else Should Be in the MVP (features that have not been asked)?
Because this product is for a Federal Reserve External Communications team, there are implicit requirements that must be included even if not spelled out:
1. Strict Responsible AI Guardrails
Already mentioned in your demo script:
•	No policy predictions
•	No financial advice
•	Human in the loop review
These are mandatory at the Fed. Not optional.
2. Auditability & Traceability
Even in MVP:
•	Show which model generated the response
•	Show inputs used for classification
•	Provide timestamp and version
Why? For a central bank communication team, traceability = non-negotiable.
3. Access Control
Even lightweight:
•	Only authenticated team members access the tool
•	Role-based “viewer vs reviewer” control if possible
4. Sanitization of User Input
Fed comms teams deal with:
•	Sensitive inquiries
•	Potentially harmful or misinformed content 

